    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lay honorary officers of a parish or district church who manage the secular affairs of parish or district churches, particularly those relating to the building and other property.  Formerly, they acted as the sole representatives of the laity of each parish in matters of church business. The term is use particularly in Episcopalian and Anglican churches.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>En las Iglesias Espiscopal y Anglicana, oficiales laicos electos que manejan los asuntos seculares de parroquias o jurisdicciones de iglesias, particularmente aquellos relacionados a la construcción y otras propiedades. Antiguamente, ellos actuaban como representante exclusivo del laicado de cada parroquia en materia de negocios de la iglesia.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In de episcopale of anglicaanse kerken zijn dit gekozen functionarissen die de niet-kerkelijke zaken van parochie- of districtskerken regelen, met name zaken die te maken hebben met het gebouw en andere eigendommen. Voorheen fungeerden ze als de enige vertegenwoordigers van de leken van iedere parochie in kerkelijke zaken.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>為一教區或區會的非神職榮譽委員，負責管理教區或區會的非宗教事務；特別與教會建築以及其他教會財產有關的事務。在過去，他們是每個教區在教會事務上唯一的非神職人員代表。此一詞彙特別用於美國新教聖公會與英國國教安立甘教會。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
